<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-12-31T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-12-31T19:00:00-05:00" n="635" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.712/–: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-12-31T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 31,
                                        1925—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>70. Your 98, December 11, 3 p.m. Department will be glad to undertake
                            negotiation of a treaty of friendship, commerce and consular rights with
                            Rumania, following as closely as possible the German Treaty. You are
                            authorized to discuss the matter with the appropriate officials and to
                            report their attitude together with any suggestions you may care to
                            submit in the matter.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
